24/06/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- EULEX arrested a man for suspected war crimes, on Wednesday (June 23rd), but did not identify him.
"EULEX's Police Executive Department, under the supervision of the Special Prosecutor's Office, carried out a house search and arrested a male suspect in connection with war crimes in Gjakova region," the EU mission said in a statement The operation was part of an investigation into the possible mistreatment of people held in Kosovo Liberation Army facilities in northern Albania during the 1998-1999 conflict.
(TV 21, RTK, Alsat, Telegrafi, Klan Kosova - 23/06/10)
